  ('CISA-00632', 1, 'Medium', 'Audit Follow-up and Remediation', 'Which of the following would provide the BEST evidence of the log monitoring tool''s effectiveness?', 'A review of the tool''s configuration settings and thresholds.', 'Evidence of successful alerts generated by the tool that were appropriately investigated and resolved.', 'Interviews with the IT security team about their understanding of the tool''s capabilities.', 'A comparison of the current security incident logs with previous audit findings.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Evidence of successful alerts generated by the tool that were appropriately investigated and resolved.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer represents the best practice approach for the scenario presented. It aligns with ISACA standards, COBIT framework principles, and proven audit methodologies. The reasoning is grounded in risk management fundamentals and control design best practices.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: In a typical enterprise scenario, the organization that follows this answer''s approach achieves better outcomes. For instance, proper implementation results in: • Reduced operational risk • Better compliance with regulations • Improved stakeholder confidence • More efficient resource allocation • Better decision-making with proper information  The alternative approaches lead to gaps, inefficiencies, or increased risk.  WHY THIS MATTERS: Adopting this best practice ensures: • Alignment with industry standards • Reduced risk of audit findings • Better business-technology outcomes • More effective control frameworks • Improved organizational maturity  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: A review of the tool''s configuration settings and thresholds. → This approach has a critical flaw: [specific reason why wrong answer is problematic relative to context]  Option C: Interviews with the IT security team about their understanding of the tool''s capabilities. → This is incomplete or applies the wrong standard. It