  ('CISA-00655', 1, 'Hard', 'Control Testing Methodologies', 'What is the MOST important action for the auditor to take FIRST?', 'Review the network configuration settings for the rate limiting and traffic shaping devices.', 'Perform penetration testing to simulate another denial-of-service attack and evaluate the effectiveness of the implemented controls under real-world conditions.', 'Examine incident response logs and post-incident reports to determine if the implemented controls were correctly triggered and effective during the past attacks.', 'Obtain documentation showing the organization''s documented maximum tolerable downtime for e-commerce services.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Examine incident response logs and post-incident reports to determine if the implemented controls were correctly triggered and effective during the past attacks.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis