  ('CISA-00656', 1, 'Hard', 'Control Testing Methodologies', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to management regarding the segregation of duties?', 'Immediately implement automated testing procedures to compensate for the lack of segregation of duties.', 'Conduct a comprehensive risk assessment to determine the potential impact of inadequate segregation of duties on the payment processing system.', 'Implement multi-factor authentication for all personnel accessing the development, testing, and production environments.', 'Restructure the project team to ensure that different individuals are responsible for developing, testing, and deploying the payment processing system.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Conduct a comprehensive risk assessment to determine the potential impact of inadequate segregation of duties on the payment processing system.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basi