  ('CISA-00683', 2, 'Hard', 'IT Strategy and Alignment', 'What is the MOST important action for the auditor to take regarding data quality in relation to the IT strategic goal of improving customer experience?', 'Verify the implementation of data loss prevention (DLP) tools to prevent unauthorized disclosure of customer data.', 'Assess the data quality controls and validation processes across all data sources to ensure accuracy, completeness, and consistency of customer data.', 'Evaluate the organization''s compliance with relevant data privacy regulations such as GDPR and CCPA.', 'Review the access controls to customer data to prevent unauthorized access and modifications.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Assess the data quality controls and validation processes across all data sources to ensure accuracy, completeness, and consistency of customer data.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • B