  ('CISA-00684', 2, 'Hard', 'IT Strategy and Alignment', 'What is the MOST important action for the auditor to recommend to the IT governance committee?', 'Conduct a post-implementation review six months after the SIS go-live to assess its technical performance and identify areas for improvement.', 'Develop and integrate key performance indicators (KPIs) into the IT strategic plan that directly link the SIS implementation to measurable improvements in student success and administrative processes.', 'Implement a change management process to address potential user resistance and ensure effective adoption of the new SIS across all departments.', 'Perform a vulnerability assessment and penetration test of the SIS to identify and mitigate potential security risks associated with student data.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Develop and integrate key performance indicators (KPIs) into the IT strategic plan that directly link the SIS implementation to measurable improvements in student success and administrative processes.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as