  ('CISA-00685', 2, 'Hard', 'IT Governance Frameworks', 'What is the FIRST action the IS auditor should recommend to the IT steering committee?', 'Immediately halt the proprietary system implementation until a formal risk assessment is conducted by the IT department.', 'Ensure a comprehensive cost-benefit analysis is performed, including long-term maintenance and potential vendor lock-in risks associated with the proprietary solution.', 'Require the development of a detailed data migration plan from legacy systems to the new proprietary research data management system.', 'Mandate a penetration test of the proprietary system after deployment to identify potential security vulnerabilities.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Ensure a comprehensive cost-benefit analysis is performed, including long-term maintenance and potential vendor lock-in risks associated with the proprietary solution.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit t