  ('CISA-00687', 2, 'Hard', 'IT Governance Frameworks', 'What is the MOST important control the IS auditor should recommend to improve IT governance in this decentralized environment?', 'Implement a centralized IT budgeting process to ensure consistent funding for security initiatives across all departments.', 'Establish a university-wide data classification policy and data security standards, enforced through regular audits and performance metrics tied to departmental budgets.', 'Consolidate all departmental IT systems into a single, centrally managed IT infrastructure to enforce uniformity.', 'Mandate the use of a standardized set of security tools and technologies across all departments to ensure consistent security practices.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Establish a university-wide data classification policy and data security standards, enforced through regular audits and performance metrics tied to departmental budgets.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • C