  ('CISA-00706', 2, 'Medium', 'Organizational Structure', 'What is the MOST important control that an auditor should recommend to mitigate this conflict of interest?', 'Implementing segregation of duties by separating CRM system administration and development functions into distinct departments.', 'Mandating regular security awareness training for all employees in the CRM department.', 'Enforcing a strict change management process for all CRM system modifications.', 'Implementing multi-factor authentication for all users accessing the CRM system.', 'A', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (A): Implementing segregation of duties by separating CRM system administration and development functions into distinct departments.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option B: Mandating regular security awareness training for all employees i