  ('CISA-00711', 2, 'Medium', 'Organizational Structure', 'What is the MOST important control the auditor should recommend to strengthen governance over the outsourced relationship?', 'Implementing a service level agreement (SLA) with clearly defined response times and performance metrics.', 'Establishing a dedicated internal team with the expertise to monitor the third-party provider''s performance and ensure compliance with security policies.', 'Performing regular vulnerability assessments on the third-party provider''s systems and infrastructure.', 'Requiring the third-party provider to maintain cyber insurance coverage to mitigate financial risks.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Establishing a dedicated internal team with the expertise to monitor the third-party provider''s performance and ensure compliance with security policies.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future fo