plementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: The model is not properly trained with enough data from fraudulent transactions. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option C: The IT department is not sufficiently monitoring the model''s resource consumption and efficiency. → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: There is a lack of segregation of duties between the data scientists who build the model and the fraud investigators who use its output. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
  ('CISA-00749', 2, 'Hard', 'Performance Measurement and KPIs', 'What is the MOST critical action for the auditor to take to mitigate the risk associated with regulatory reporting?', 'Review the cloud provider''s Service Level Agreement (SLA) to ensure it includes provisions for regulatory compliance.', 'Recommend that management establish a process to map regulatory reporting requirements to the data and processes within the cloud-based core banking system.', 'Verify that the cloud provider has obtained the necessary certifications and attestations to demonstrate compliance with relevant regulations.', 'Assess the security controls implemented by the cloud provider to protect sensitive customer data.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Recommend that management establish a process to map regulatory reporting requirements to the data and processes within the cloud-based core banking system.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audi