  ('CISA-00757', 2, 'Hard', 'Performance Measurement and KPIs', 'What is the PRIMARY concern for the CISA auditor regarding the use of KPIs in this scenario?', 'The lack of technical expertise within the business units to interpret the performance reports.', 'The potential for misinterpretation of performance data leading to incorrect business decisions.', 'The disconnect between IT performance metrics and business strategic objectives, hindering the value of IT investments.', 'The increased operational costs associated with maintaining multiple performance measurement tools and reporting systems.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): The disconnect between IT performance metrics and business strategic objectives, hindering the value of IT investments.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: The lack of technical