  ('CISA-00758', 2, 'Hard', 'Performance Measurement and KPIs', 'What is the MOST important control that should be established to address this oversight?', 'A post-implementation review process that includes an assessment of IT performance against SLAs and business outcomes.', 'A formal change management process to control modifications to the CRM system and its associated KPIs.', 'Automated reporting on IT performance metrics and their alignment with defined service level objectives.', 'Periodic security vulnerability assessments to ensure the CRM system is protected from external threats.', 'A', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (A): A post-implementation review process that includes an assessment of IT performance against SLAs and business outcomes.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer represents the best practice approach for the scenario presented. It aligns with ISACA standards, COBIT framework principles, and proven audit methodologies. The reasoning is grounded in risk management fundamentals and control design best practices.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: In a typical enterprise scenario, the organization that follows this answer''s approach achieves better outcomes. For instance, proper implementation results in: • Reduced operational risk • Better compliance with regulations • Improved stakeholder confidence • More efficient resource allocation • Better decision-making with proper information  The alternative approaches lead to gaps, inefficiencies, or increased risk.  WHY THIS MATTERS: Adopting this best practice ensures: • Alignment with industry standards • Reduced risk of audit findings • Better business-technology outcomes • More effective control frameworks • Improved organizational maturity  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option B: A formal change management process to control modifications to the CRM system and its associated KPIs. → This approach has a critical flaw: [specific reason why wrong answer is problematic relative to context]  Option C: Automated