ffective control frameworks • Improved organizational maturity  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option B: A formal change management process to control modifications to the CRM system and its associated KPIs. → This approach has a critical flaw: [specific reason why wrong answer is problematic relative to context]  Option C: Automated reporting on IT performance metrics and their alignment with defined service level objectives. → This is incomplete or applies the wrong standard. It might address part of the issue but misses the full picture.  Option D: Periodic security vulnerability assessments to ensure the CRM system is protected from external threats. → While seemingly reasonable, this approach deviates from best practice and creates unnecessary risk or inefficiency.'),
