  ('CISA-00796', 2, 'Hard', 'IT Portfolio Management', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to management?', 'Approve the new fraud detection initiative and secure the required resources from other departments.', 'Prioritize the new fraud detection initiative over all other existing projects within the IT portfolio.', 'Conduct a comprehensive gap analysis of the current IT portfolio to identify resource constraints and infrastructure limitations before approving the new initiative.', 'Procure additional hardware and software licenses to accommodate the new fraud detection initiative without assessing its impact on the overall IT portfolio.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Conduct a comprehensive gap analysis of the current IT portfolio to identify resource constraints and infrastructure limitations before approving the new initiative.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future