  ('CISA-00801', 2, 'Medium', 'IT Portfolio Management', 'What is the MOST important control that should be implemented to prevent this issue in future migrations?', 'Implement strong data encryption at rest and in transit for all patient data.', 'Establish a comprehensive data governance framework with clear data ownership, quality standards, and metadata management.', 'Deploy an intrusion detection system (IDS) to monitor for unauthorized access to patient data.', 'Conduct regular penetration testing to identify vulnerabilities in the cloud environment.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Establish a comprehensive data governance framework with clear data ownership, quality standards, and metadata management.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer represents the best practice approach for the scenario presented. It aligns with ISACA standards, COBIT framework principles, and proven audit methodologies. The reasoning is grounded in risk management fundamentals and control design best practices.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: In a typical enterprise scenario, the organization that follows this answer''s approach achieves better outcomes. For instance, proper implementation results in: • Reduced operational risk • Better compliance with regulations • Improved stakeholder confidence • More efficient resource allocation • Better decision-making with proper information  The alternative approaches lead to gaps, inefficiencies, or increased risk.  WHY THIS MATTERS: Adopting this best practice ensures: • Alignment with industry standards • Reduced risk of audit findings • Better business-technology outcomes • More effective control frameworks • Improved organizational maturity  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Implement strong data encryption at rest and in transit for all patient data. → This approach has a critical flaw: [specific reason why wrong answer is problematic relative to context]  Option C: Deploy an intrusion detection system (IDS) to monitor for unauthor