ch has a critical flaw: [specific reason why wrong answer is problematic relative to context]  Option C: Deploy an intrusion detection system (IDS) to monitor for unauthorized access to patient data. → This is incomplete or applies the wrong standard. It might address part of the issue but misses the full picture.  Option D: Conduct regular penetration testing to identify vulnerabilities in the cloud environment. → While seemingly reasonable, this approach deviates from best practice and creates unnecessary risk or inefficiency.'),
