  ('CISA-00835', 3, 'Medium', 'Agile and Waterfall Methodologies', 'What is the MOST important action for the auditor to take?', 'Recommend immediate system shutdown until a full security assessment can be conducted.', 'Recommend a retrospective analysis to identify the root cause of the requirement gaps and prevent recurrence in future projects.', 'Request the development team to immediately implement security patches to address the identified vulnerabilities.', 'Issue a qualified audit opinion highlighting the non-compliance with security standards and recommend immediate remediation.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Recommend a retrospective analysis to identify the root cause of the requirement gaps and prevent recurrence in future projects.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Recommend immediate sys