  ('CISA-00847', 3, 'Hard', 'Software Quality Assurance', 'What is the MOST important control that should be implemented to address this deficiency?', 'Implement a secure coding training program for the development team.', 'Establish a formal change management process for all code modifications.', 'Require the development team to document the security design rationale for each feature and modification.', 'Implement a vulnerability scanning program to identify potential security flaws in the code.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Require the development team to document the security design rationale for each feature and modification.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer represents the best practice approach for the scenario presented. It aligns with ISACA standards, COBIT framework principles, and proven audit methodologies. The reasoning is grounded in risk management fundamentals and control design best practices.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: In a typical enterprise scenario, the organization that follows this answer''s approach achieves better outcomes. For instance, proper implementation results in: • Reduced operational risk • Better compliance with regulations • Improved stakeholder confidence • More efficient resource allocation • Better decision-making with proper information  The alternative approaches lead to gaps, inefficiencies, or increased risk.  WHY THIS MATTERS: Adopting this best practice ensures: • Alignment with industry standards • Reduced risk of audit findings • Better business-technology outcomes • More effective control frameworks • Improved organizational maturity  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Implement a secure coding training program for the development team. → This approach has a critical flaw: [specific reason why wrong answer is problematic relative to context]  Option B: Establish a formal change management process for all code modifications. → This is incomplete or applies the wrong standard. It might address part of th