  ('CISA-00848', 3, 'Hard', 'Software Quality Assurance', 'What is the MOST important action for the auditor to take?', 'Recommend increasing the size and skill set of the QA team to improve test coverage.', 'Evaluate the documentation related to the AI model''s development, training, and validation to understand its design and limitations.', 'Require the implementation of a comprehensive data lineage program to trace the origin and transformations of data used by the AI model.', 'Advise that the organization engage an external AI specialist to assist in developing appropriate test cases and validating the AI model''s accuracy.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Evaluate the documentation related to the AI model''s development, training, and validation to understand its design and limitations.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why The