ation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Recommend increasing the size and skill set of the QA team to improve test coverage. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option C: Require the implementation of a comprehensive data lineage program to trace the origin and transformations of data used by the AI model. → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: Advise that the organization engage an external AI specialist to assist in developing appropriate test cases and validating the AI model''s accuracy. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
  ('CISA-00849', 3, 'Hard', 'Data Migration and Testing', 'What is the MOST important action for the auditor to take in this situation?', 'Review the data transformation scripts to identify and resolve any potential errors in the data mapping process.', 'Assess the organization''s data migration plan, focusing on the testing methodology, data validation procedures, and remediation strategies for identified errors.', 'Verify that the project team has obtained documented approval from the Chief Information Security Officer (CISO) for the data migration strategy.', 'Conduct penetration testing on the new EHR system to identify potential vulnerabilities after the data migration.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Assess the organization''s data migration plan, focusing on the testing methodology, data validation procedures, and remediation strategies for identified errors.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for complianc