  ('CISA-00853', 3, 'Hard', 'Data Migration and Testing', 'If the test data migration reveals inconsistencies in equipment calibration data in the new system, what action should the auditor recommend as the FIRST priority?', 'Review the system logs to determine if any unauthorized access or data manipulation occurred during the test migration.', 'Investigate the data transformation rules and scripts to identify and correct any errors in the data conversion process specific to calibration data.', 'Implement enhanced data encryption and access controls on the new system to prevent future data inconsistencies.', 'Repeat the test migration with a larger sample of calibration data to confirm the extent and consistency of the data discrepancies.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Investigate the data transformation rules and scripts to identify and correct any errors in the data conversion process specific to calibration data.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accou