  ('CISA-00854', 3, 'Hard', 'Data Migration and Testing', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend?', 'Implement a rollback plan to the original system as a contingency measure if data corruption is detected post-migration.', 'Conduct a thorough review of the change management process to ensure that all changes to the ETL processes and validation rules are properly authorized, tested, and documented.', 'Increase the frequency of data integrity checks during the migration to identify and correct any discrepancies as they occur.', 'Implement enhanced monitoring of the new platform post-migration to detect any performance issues related to the data format changes.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Conduct a thorough review of the change management process to ensure that all changes to the ETL processes and validation rules are properly authorized, tested, and documented.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for complianc