  ('CISA-00855', 3, 'Hard', 'Data Migration and Testing', 'What is the MOST important control the auditor should assess?', 'The adequacy of the disaster recovery plan to ensure business continuity in case of system failure during peak traffic.', 'The effectiveness of the load testing and performance tuning processes to identify and address bottlenecks in the new system.', 'The completeness and accuracy of the data migration process to ensure that all customer data is transferred to the new system without errors.', 'The security controls implemented to protect customer data in the cloud environment, including encryption and access controls.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): The effectiveness of the load testing and performance tuning processes to identify and address bottlenecks in the new system.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why