  ('CISA-00857', 3, 'Hard', 'Data Migration and Testing', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to mitigate risks?', 'Implement transaction monitoring rules to detect unusual patterns, like very large or unusual transactions.', 'Perform a comprehensive data validation exercise involving end-users and production-like data volume and variety.', 'Review the application logs regularly for errors that could be indicators of faulty data mapping.', 'Immediately suspend usage of the new payment gateway until a complete security vulnerability scan is complete.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Perform a comprehensive data validation exercise involving end-users and production-like data volume and variety.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Implement transaction monitoring rules to detect unusual patterns, like