  ('CISA-00859', 3, 'Hard', 'Data Migration and Testing', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to ensure data compliance during migration?', 'Implement data encryption across all regions, regardless of residency regulations, as a uniform security measure.', 'Prioritize the creation of a comprehensive data classification and mapping exercise that details data residency requirements for each data element involved in the migration.', 'Conduct penetration testing on the target billing system to identify vulnerabilities after the migration is complete.', 'Develop a rollback plan to revert the migration in case of technical issues.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Prioritize the creation of a comprehensive data classification and mapping exercise that details data residency requirements for each data element involved in the migration.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follo