  ('CISA-00886', 3, 'Hard', 'Project Management Controls', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to ensure regulatory compliance with data residency requirements?', 'Mandate the vendor provide a Service Organization Control (SOC) 2 report detailing their security controls related to data storage and processing.', 'Review the vendor''s data residency policies and compare them to the institution''s regulatory obligations before implementation begins.', 'Request the vendor provide a data encryption key management plan detailing how data at rest and in transit will be protected.', 'Implement a data loss prevention (DLP) solution to monitor and prevent sensitive research data from leaving the approved cloud environment.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Review the vendor''s data residency policies and compare them to the institution''s regulatory obligations before implementation begins.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit t