  ('CISA-00899', 3, 'Medium', 'Vendor and Contract Management', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend to ensure the healthcare provider can effectively monitor the vendor''s performance against the SLAs?', 'Implement a system to automatically generate reports detailing the vendor''s compliance with all contractual obligations.', 'Establish clear metrics, monitoring procedures, and reporting mechanisms to track the vendor''s performance against the SLAs.', 'Conduct periodic penetration testing on the EHR system to assess its security posture.', 'Ensure that the vendor has undergone a SOC 2 Type II audit and review the audit report.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Establish clear metrics, monitoring procedures, and reporting mechanisms to track the vendor''s performance against the SLAs.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They'